150 grams Prawns
120 grams Salad Leaves
1 unit(s) Grated Italian Style Hard Cheese
1 unit(s) Cucumber
1 sachet(s) Aioli
1 sachet(s) Paprika
2 unit(s) Tomato
to taste Salt
to taste Pepper
to taste Oil

Place a pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.
Once hot, add the prawns. Season with paprika, salt and pepper.
Fry until cooked through, 4-5 mins. Once cooked, remove the pan from the heat. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw prawns. Prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Meanwhile, halve the cucumber lengthways then thinly slice widthways.
Chop the tomatoes into 2cm chunks.
Trim the salad leaves and roughly chop.

To a large bowl, add salad leaves, cucumber, tomatoes, aioli and cheese.
Toss until fully combined then season to taste with salt and pepper.
Divide the Ceasar salad between plates and top with the fried prawns.